<s> Cipher Data Products Inc. posted a net loss of $ 14.2 million , or 97 cents a share , for its fiscal first quarter , compared with net income of $ 3.8 million , or 27 cents a share , a year ago . </s>
<s> Revenue for the quarter ended Sept. 30 fell 20 % , to $ 41.3 million from $ 51.9 million in the year-earlier period . </s>
<s> Cipher Data , a San Diego maker of magnetic tape peripherals and optical disc drives , said the loss included reserves of $ 3.8 million related to a corporate restructuring . </s>
<s> The restructuring calls for a 24 % reduction in its work force over the next two months , affecting about 525 jobs , Cipher Data said . </s>
<s> It is eliminating the positions of president and chief operating officer , formerly held by Edward L. Marinaro . </s>
<s> Cipher Data said Mr. Marinaro consequently has resigned from those posts and from the company 's board . </s>
<s> Mr. Marinaro could n't immediately be reached for comment . </s>
